Gemini saidSmart Routing & Rider Updates!


Ground operations can change in a heartbeat.

In order to tackle it we have Multiple different tasks going together hand
in hand.







*Forward/Reverse Order Merging*



This update introduces the ability to seamlessly club forward and reverse
orders together. This enhancement will streamline the routing process and
optimize rider efficiency



*Repritoritization of Tasks*Depending on whether it's a forward or reverse
task, any nearby order that can be finished on time can now be prioritized
accordingly.



*Top Rider Enhancement*



We are introducing a new new sorting and filtering constraint in the "Top
Rider" selection logic based on *Rider's Free Time*


Why We Built These?







*Forward/Reverse order merging*


By allowing the system to safely "club" these orders together, it prevents
riders from having to make redundant trips, ultimately making the routing
process smoother and more cost-effective.


*Reprioritization*

We took care of reprioritization to bridge the gap between fixed route
planning and on-the-ground reality. Riders need agility to maximize their
daily earnings and avoid SLA penalties, but businesses still need
operational safeguards to protect cash collection and order dependencies.


*Top Rider Enhancement*

System filters and identifies riders who have been free and then it applies
the existing distance logic to those filtered riders first ensuring
equitable order disttribution




What=E2=80=99s New!


Combined Forward & Reverse Routes


*Smart Route Clubbing:* The system now officially supports bundling forward
(delivery) and reverse (pickup/return) orders together into a single,
automated route.



You no longer need to manually piece together forward and reverse orders
for a single rider to avoid system crashes. The system can now handle
automated bundling safely.







Repritoritization of Tasks

   1.

   *Rearrange Live tasks:* Riders can now reprioritize/rearrange pickup and
   drop tasks, even within complex merged routes.

   When a rider selects a new priority, it instantly becomes the single *Li=
ve
   Task*, pushing the previous live task back into the queue sequence.


   2.

   *Built-in Guardrails:* To prevent delivery mistakes, riders are strictly
   blocked from prioritizing a drop task before its associated pickup has
   actually occurred. Also,  If a rider marks themselves as *Reached* at a
   pickup or delivery location, the system locks the route sequence to prev=
ent
   accidental changes while they are finalizing the order.




Top Riders Algorithm


15-Minute Smart Filter: There is a default 15-minute threshold of free
riders. It first filters and isolates riders who have been free for 15
minutes or more before applying standard distance metrics


What This Means To You






   1.

   *Cost & Route Optimization:* By seamlessly combining deliveries and
   returns into unified routes, you can significantly reduce total distance
   traveled, save fuel, and cut down on overall operational costs.


   2.

   *Maximizing Rider Flexibility: *Controlled, on-the-ground task
   reordering for delivery riders, allowing them to dynamically prioritize
   single pickup or drop tasks to handle real-world delays and still
   protecting operational integrity and SLAs.


   3.

   *Faster, Friction-Free Allocation:* The prefers allocation to free
   riders allowing rider optimization.

What=E2=80=99s Next

Something exciting is coming soon - Stay tuned !!
